resource/Raygun\"}, {\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999999992442099, \"rank\": 6.969349234514008e-10, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 583, \"end\": 592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999546481347055, \"rank\": 4.509112527924001e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 36-year-old professor\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"internet fame\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 624}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic-level skill\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competing against some b-girls half her age, she was swept out of the round-robin stage without earning a single point, and her unconventional moves landed flat while failing to match the skill level of her foes.\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 883, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some b-girls\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 701}, {\"ngram\": \"the round-robin stage\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"a single point\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"her unconventional moves\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 819}, {\"ngram\": \"the skill level\", \"from\": 855, \"to\": 870}, {\"ngram\": \"her foes\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up for our Daily eBlast to get coverage on Black communities from the media company who has been doing it right for over 133 years.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our Daily eBlast\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 913}, {\"ngram\": \"coverage\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 929}, {\"ngram\": \"Black communities\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 950}, {\"ngram\": \"the media company\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 973}, {\"ngram\": \"over 133 years\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1020}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At one point, Gunn raised one leg while standing and leaned back with her arms bent toward her ears.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1037, \"end\": 1041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.8658659861290644, \"rank\": 0.14929970505025028, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1035}, {\"ngram\": \"one leg\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"her arms\", \"from\": 1093, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"her ears\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1122}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At another, while laying on her side, she reached for her toes, flipped over and did it again in a move dubbed \\\"the kangaroo.\\\"\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1250, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1134}, {\"ngram\": \"her side\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"her toes\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"a move\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the kangaroo\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gunn has a Ph.D. in cultural studies, and her LinkedIn page notes she is \\\"interested in the cultural politics of breaking.\\\"\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.8658659861290644, \"rank\": 0.14929970505025028, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}, {\"begin\": 1298, \"end\": 1306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LinkedIn\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LinkedIn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Ph.D.\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"cultural studies\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1288}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultural politics\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was never going to beat these girls on what they do best - their power moves,\\\" said Gunn.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1464, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.8658659861290644, \"rank\": 0.14929970505025028, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Gunn\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these girls\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"their power moves\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What I bring is creativity.\\\"\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1499, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"creativity\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1497}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Clips of her routine have gone viral on TikTok and elsewhere, and many cringed at her moves platformed on the Olympic stage as a representation of hip-hop and breaking culture.\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1541, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1840759780986616e-57, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Clips\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"her routine\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"her moves\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic stage\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1624}, {\"ngram\": \"a representation\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1655}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking culture\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1676}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's almost like they are mocking the genre,\\\" wrote one user on X.\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1746, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the genre\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"one user\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"X.\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1746}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of it was 'weird to see' Many Black viewers, in particular, called out Lithuania's silver medalist b-girl Nicka, (legally named Dominika Banevi\\u010d) for donning a durag during each of her battles.\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.6545585804277128, \"rank\": 0.5277471312028487, \"text\": \"Lithuania\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuania_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"' Many Black viewers\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"Dominika Banevi\\u010d\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"a durag\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngram\": \"her battles\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1945}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durags, once worn by enslaved Africans to tie up their hair for work, are still worn by Black people to protect and style their hair.\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slavery_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999957092378475, \"rank\": 4.290609365454308e-06, \"text\": \"enslaved Africans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slavery_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slavery_in_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Durags\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1954}, {\"ngram\": \"their hair\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"Black people\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2048}, {\"ngram\": \"their hair\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They became a fashionable symbol of Black pride in the 1960s and 1970s and, in the 1990s and early 2000s, also became a popular element of hip-hop style.\", \"from\": 2082, \"to\": 2235, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fashionable symbol\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2114}, {\"ngram\": \"Black pride\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2129}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1960s\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2142}, {\"ngram\": \"1970s\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2152}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1990s\", \"from\": 2161, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"early 2000s\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2186}, {\"ngram\": \"a popular element\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2217}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop style\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when worn by those who are not Black, durags can be seen as cultural appropriation.\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"durags\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2285}, {\"ngram\": \"cultural appropriation\", \"from\": 2301, \"to\": 2323}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Banevi\\u010d is White.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2342, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Banevi\\u010d\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Actor Kevin Fredericks responded on Instagram to Banevi\\u010d donning the headwear by saying it looked \\\"weird to see somebody who do not need it for protective style or waves to be rocking the durag.\\\"\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2380, \"end\": 2389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0680223130243049e-39, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Actor Kevin Fredericks\", \"from\": 2344, \"to\": 2366}, {\"ngram\": \"Banevi\\u010d\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2400}, {\"ngram\": \"the headwear\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2421}, {\"ngram\": \"somebody\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"protective style\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2504}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2513}, {\"ngram\": \"the durag\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 17-year-old breaker ultimately won the silver medal after losing in the final to Japan's b-girl Ami (Ami Yuasa).\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2657, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2626, \"end\": 2631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9991172770722705, \"rank\": 0.000837329060387691, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 17-year-old breaker\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2564}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver medal\", \"from\": 2580, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"Ami Yuasa\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2655}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For her part, Banevi\\u010d has credited the breakers from the 1970s in the Bronx - the OGs - or \\\"original gangsters\\\" in hip-hop who created the dance - for her own success and breaking style.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2729, \"end\": 2734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.945358877802693e-14, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her part\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"Banevi\\u010d\", \"from\": 2673, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"the breakers\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2706}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1970s\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2721}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"original gangsters\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2769}, {\"ngram\": \"hip-hop\", \"from\": 2774, \"to\": 2781}, {\"ngram\": \"the dance\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2803}, {\"ngram\": \"her own success\", \"from\": 2810, \"to\": 2825}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking style\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a huge responsibility to represent and raise the bar every time for breaking because they did an amazing job.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2962, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a huge responsibility\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"the bar\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"an amazing job\", \"from\": 2947, \"to\": 2961}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Big respect for the OGs and the pioneers that invented all those moves.\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Big respect\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 2974}, {\"ngram\": \"the OGs\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 2986}, {\"ngram\": \"the pioneers\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 3003}, {\"ngram\": \"all those moves\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without them, it would not be possible,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3085, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Without them, breaking would not be where it is today.\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3141, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 3101, \"to\": 3109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I am grateful for them.\\\"\", \"from\": 3142, \"to\": 3169, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Concerns over losing breaking's roots The slips \\\"may have alienated too many new viewers to garner the anticipated response from our Olympic premiere,\\\" said Zack Slusser, vice president of Breaking for Gold USA and USA Dance, in a text message to the Associated Press.\", \"from\": 3171, \"to\": 3440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3329, \"end\": 3333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Montana\", \"score\": 0.9999999997125997, \"rank\": 2.4056178277956515e-10, \"text\": \"Zack\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Montana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Montana\"}, {\"begin\": 3423, \"end\": 3439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999990658584281, \"rank\": 9.341426449439572e-07, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Concerns\", \"from\": 3171, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking's roots\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3208}, {\"ngram\": \"The slips\", \"from\": 3209, \"to\": 3218}, {\"ngram\": \"too many new viewers\", \"from\": 3239, \"to\": 3259}, {\"ngram\": \"the anticipated response\", \"from\": 3270, \"to\": 3294}, {\"ngram\": \"our Olympic premiere\", \"from\": 3300, \"to\": 3320}, {\"ngram\": \"vice president\", \"from\": 3342, \"to\": 3356}, {\"ngram\": \"Breaking\", \"from\": 3360, \"to\": 3368}, {\"ngram\": \"Gold USA\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3381}, {\"ngram\": \"USA Dance\", \"from\": 3386, \"to\": 3395}, {\"ngram\": \"a text message\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3414}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need to change the narrative from yesterday's first impression of breaking as Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the narrative\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3474}, {\"ngram\": \"yesterday's first impression\", \"from\": 3480, \"to\": 3508}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic sport\", \"from\": 3524, \"to\": 3537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were significant organizational and governance shortcomings that could have been easily reconciled but, unfortunately, negatively impacted Breaking's first touching point to a new global audience.\\\"\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 3742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"significant organizational and governance shortcomings\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3604}, {\"ngram\": \"Breaking's first touching point\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 3715}, {\"ngram\": \"a new global audience\", \"from\": 3719, \"to\": 3740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The challenge for Olympic organizers was to bring breaking and hip-hop culture to a mass audience, including many viewers who were skeptical about the dance form's addition to the Olympic roster.\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3939, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The challenge\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3757}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic organizers\", \"from\": 3762, \"to\": 3780}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking and hip-hop culture\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3822}, {\"ngram\": \"a mass audience\", \"from\": 3826, \"to\": 3841}, {\"ngram\": \"many viewers\", \"from\": 3853, \"to\": 3865}, {\"ngram\": \"the dance form's addition\", \"from\": 3891, \"to\": 3916}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic roster\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 3938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others feared the subculture being co-opted by officials, commercialized and put through a rigid judging structure, when the spirit of breaking has been rooted in local communities, centered around street battles, cyphers and block parties.\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 4180, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Others\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 3946}, {\"ngram\": \"the subculture\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 3968}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 3987, \"to\": 3996}, {\"ngram\": \"a rigid judging structure\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4054}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 4061, \"to\": 4071}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking\", \"from\": 4075, \"to\": 4083}, {\"ngram\": \"local communities\", \"from\": 4103, \"to\": 4120}, {\"ngram\": \"street battles\", \"from\": 4138, \"to\": 4152}, {\"ngram\": \"cyphers\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4161}, {\"ngram\": \"block parties\", \"from\": 4166, \"to\": 4179}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hip-hop was born as a youth culture within Black and Brown communities in the Bronx as a way to escape strife and socio-economic struggles and make a statement of empowerment at a time when they were labeled as lost, lawless kids by New York politicians.\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4224, \"end\": 4229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 0.9978415835645124, \"rank\": 0.0021630852746215724, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}, {\"begin\": 4259, \"end\": 4264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.945358877802693e-14, \"text\": \"Bronx\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bronx\"}, {\"begin\": 4414, \"end\": 4422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.964747851011701e-13, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hip-hop\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4188}, {\"ngram\": \"a youth culture\", \"from\": 4201, \"to\": 4216}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 4268, \"to\": 4273}, {\"ngram\": \"strife\", \"from\": 4284, \"to\": 4290}, {\"ngram\": \"socio-economic struggles\", \"from\": 4295, \"to\": 4319}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 4329, \"to\": 4340}, {\"ngram\": \"empowerment\", \"from\": 4344, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 4359, \"to\": 4365}, {\"ngram\": \"lost, lawless kids\", \"from\": 4392, \"to\": 4410}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Refugee breaker Manizha Talash, or \\\"b-girl Talash,\\\" channeled that rebellious vibe by donning a \\\"Free Afghan Women\\\" cape during her pre-qualifier battle - a defiant and personal statement for a 21-year-old who fled her native Afghanistan to escape Taliban rule.\", \"from\": 4437, \"to\": 4698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4453, \"end\": 4460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Manizha\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manizha\"}, {\"begin\": 4461, \"end\": 4467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\", \"score\": 0.858682698055531, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Talash\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Talash_(1969_film)\"}, {\"begin\": 4663, \"end\": 4674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999997235545761, \"rank\": 2.764285679597758e-07, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 4685, \"end\": 4692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"score\": 0.999793950773706, \"rank\": 0.00020609169048857112, \"text\": \"Taliban\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taliban\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"b-girl Talash\", \"from\": 4472, \"to\": 4486}, {\"ngram\": \"that rebellious vibe\", \"from\": 4499, \"to\": 4519}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"Free Afghan Women\\\" cape\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4557}, {\"ngram\": \"her pre-qualifier battle\", \"from\": 4565, \"to\": 4589}, {\"ngram\": \"a defiant and personal statement\", \"from\": 4592, \"to\": 4624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Talash was quickly disqualified for violating the Olympics' ban on political statements on the field of play.\", \"from\": 4699, \"to\": 4808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Talash\", \"from\": 4699, \"t